quotes.author: Alexander the Great
quotes.content: An army of sheep led by a lion is better than an army of lions led by a sheep

quotes.author: Mahatma Gandhi
quotes.content: Be the change that you wish to see in the world

quotes.author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
quotes.content: Show me a hero, and I'll write you a tragedy

quotes.author: Bob Dylan
quotes.content: When you ain't got nothing, you got nothing to lose

quotes.author: Albert Einstein
quotes.content: The only source of knowledge is experience

quotes.author: Winston Churchill
quotes.content: Success is not final, failure is not fatal: It is the courage to continue that counts

quotes.author: Napoleon Bonaparte
quotes.content: Victory belongs to the most persevering

quotes.author: Walt Disney
quotes.content: The way to get started is to quit talking and begin doing

quotes.author: Steve Jobs
quotes.content: Your work is going to fill a large part of your life, and the only way to be truly satisfied is to do what you believe is great work. And the only way to do great work is to love what you do. If you haven't found it yet, keep looking. Don't settle. As with all matters of the heart, you'll know when you find it

quotes.author: Steve Jobs
quotes.content: Your time is limited, don't waste it living someone else's life. Don't be trapped by dogma, which is living the result of other people's thinking. Don't let the noise of other opinions drown your own inner voice. And most important, have the courage to follow your heart and intuition, they somehow already know what you truly want to become. Everything else is secondary
